    <briefdescription>
<para>Abstract base class for built-in USB Serial/JTAG controller wrappers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Mirrors the lazy-initialise / Read / Write / Flush shape of <computeroutput><ref refid="classBaseUart" kindref="compound">BaseUart</ref></computeroutput> so a <computeroutput>ConsoleSerialTransport</computeroutput> can hold either a <computeroutput>BaseUart*</computeroutput> or a <computeroutput>BaseUsbSerialJtag*</computeroutput> behind a tiny adapter.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Not inherently thread-safe. The underlying ESP-IDF driver is safe for concurrent reader/writer callers, but if you wrap it with stateful helpers (e.g. printf) protect them with a mutex. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
